HEADWORD: expressed
<hw>expressed</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Communicated in
words.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> uttered, verbalized.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Precisely and clearly expressed, leaving nothing to
implication. Opposite of <ant>implicit</ant>.</def> [Narrower terms:
<stype>graphic</stype>] <see>Also See: <er>definite</er>,
<er>denotative</er>, <er>denotive</er>, <er>overt</er>, <er>open</er>,
<er>unequivocal</er>, <er>unambiguous</er>.</see>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> explicit, express.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expressible</ent>⟦br⟧
